texts.text: Cant hold on... Any longer...
*Hiss*
>The giant Illuyanka continues its assault.
>But a sound different from the attack rings out a moment later.
All sequences complete! All sequences complete!
Okay! It's time! Back off when I give you the signal!

1!
Now, [sys user_name]!
Initiating Zwei Wind!
W-What's going on?
>It starts out as a breeze.
>Then the breeze catches the water on the ground and hurls it up into the air.
W-W-Whoa! The wind!
What is this? I-I'm getting blown away!
>The wind quickly increases velocity, blowing away all moisture within the room.
Hey look! Down there!
Wow... The Illuyanka are being blown away!
And look!
*Hiss*
Some of the water's getting in, but the giant monster itself can't break through!
Fshuuuu...
Did it work...?
Take a look! That tidal wave isn't even doing any damage!
It worked! It totally worked! We did it!
>As if emboldened by the people's cheers, the wind grows even stronger,
>until you realize you're in the eye of a typhoon.
Ha... Hahaha... We did it... We really did it...
I can't thank you two enough.
This is our anti-demon barrier system "Zwei Wind".
Zwei...?
The name means dual winds.
It was what people called us, Naito and I.
It's what we were going to name the system when it was finished.
As a monument to our friendship...
But...
"A dishonorable man who stole the women his friend loved and ran away in the middle of the project".
That's probably what he thinks of himself.
He's old fashioned like that.
But me, I don't hold any grudges against him now.
What?
He was the one who encouraged me and spurred me on to finish the project.
That's why I put everything I had into the project, because
I wanted to make this city a safe place for him and his family to live,
so he can come back and tell me all about his marriage without guilt.
Yes there were times when I hated him for what he did.
Trust is something that takes a long time to build,
but can be easily destroyed in an instant.
You make one bad choice or say one thing wrong and it's gone.
But you said you hold no grudges...
Yes.
Because I know what gets torn down can be rebuilt.
Just like the walls and defenses of this city.
I believe that if you persevere and face your challenges as they come without giving up, someday even this situation with the world will be resolved.
That's why I built the barrier system, so this city can be a symbol of man's ability to overcome adversity.
It's the same with relationships.
Ties can be severed, but you can always build back up the trust you lost if you are willing enough.
Yes... I truly believe that we can rebuild whenever we want.
Listen up everyone! If you're really considering joining the Acolytes,
then we ain't friends no more!
Are you gonna choose this...
even if it means turnin' against me?
Newbie... We're all Liberators... Aight?
So just... don't go man, c'mon!
...? ...You alright?

Are you alright [sys user_name]?
Is there something wrong?
It's nothing.
What's past is past.
What's past is past.
Well anyways, our work here's not done yet.
There are still problems we need to work out with this barrier system.
Even though it's working great?
The problem's with the power.
We don't know how long we can keep the barrier running with the fuel we have left,
and the city will need power to run on as well.
So that's the first issue we have to tackle.
More "power" to you.
You'll pull through. No problem.

*Chuckle*
Thank you.
I'll do my best.
>You hand Hagimoto a package.
What's this?
This is what we came here to give you!
Then let's see what's inside...
What a beautiful stone. And there's note. The stone is called... Eye of the Storm God ?
And what's this...?
T-This wing pendant! Where did you get it?!
What the...?
Where'd they go?
>Hagimoto looks up, only to find that [sys user_name] and Pixie are gone.

This... This is my request...
Please, take this to Shinagawa city...
Wow! What a beautiful rock!
Give it to Hagimoto of Shinagawa. That's right, Hagimoto...
What's this rock though, mister?
It's called the Eye of the Storm God.
It can generate unlimited energy...
It's the missing piece in our project...
How did you come by this?
Why are you giving it away?
...The city we escaped to... It was... attacked by demons shortly after we got there...
My wife and unborn child both...
It was probably punishment for my sins...
After that, I've been dead inside...
But then I heard about how Hagimoto was continuing the project.
Hagimoto... I have no doubt that one day you'll accomplish what we set out to do.
Because it was the light of your optimism that kept me going all these years...
But there's one last problem to solve, the power supply...
I searched far and wide, and finally I was able to find the stone that can solve this problem.
It is the solution...
And for someone who will never be able to stand beside you again, it's my final...
Okay mister, I understand...

And... One more thing...
Take this...
What's this? A wing shaped stone?
It's just a pendant. Something from our youth...
If... If he finds it in his heart to forgive me,
please give the pendant to him as well.
It was something that we gave each other, as a token of our friendship...
My one and only... Friend...
Dual winds... Lifting two wings up in the sky... Flying free...

If you persevere and don't give up...
Someday... You'll...
